"{\"abstract\":\"We investigate adaptive ensemble weighting for Neural Machine Translation, addressing the case of improving performance on a new and potentially unknown domain without sacrificing performance on the original domain. We adapt sequentially across two Spanish-English and three English-German tasks, comparing unregularized fine-tuning, L2 and Elastic Weight Consolidation. We then report a novel scheme for adaptive NMT ensemble decoding by extending Bayesian Interpolation with source information, and report strong improvements across test domains without access to the domain label.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"38635490\",\"name\":\"Danielle Saunders\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/38635490\"},{\"authorId\":\"48404632\",\"name\":\"Felix Stahlberg\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/48404632\"},{\"authorId\":\"1738657356\",\"name\":\"Adri\\u00e0 de Gispert\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1738657356\"},{\"authorId\":\"36126076\",\"name\":\"B. Byrne\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/36126076\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[],\"corpusId\":219309912,\"doi\":\"10.18653/v1/P19-1022\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":null,\"influentialCitationCount\":0,\"is_open_access\":true,\"is_publisher_licensed\":true,\"paperId\":\"2f0a335774934573487fb38f28a55892020e2730\",\"references\":[],\"title\":\"Domain Adaptive Inference for Neural Machine Translation\",\"topics\":[{\"topic\":\"Neural machine translation\",\"topicId\":\"210523\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/topic/210523\"},{\"topic\":\"Interpolation\",\"topicId\":\"1131\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/topic/1131\"},{\"topic\":\"Domain adaptation\",\"topicId\":\"41709\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/topic/41709\"},{\"topic\":\"Conformal loop ensemble\",\"topicId\":\"2894037\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/topic/2894037\"},{\"topic\":\"Semiconductor consolidation\",\"topicId\":\"3626992\"